  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the most effective treatment for patients who
      underwent a Roux-en-Y gastric bypass and developed postoperatively a vitamin B12 deficiency.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Vitamin B12 deficiency accounts up to 23-64% bariatric surgery. The investigators purpose is
      to evaluate the most effective treatment for vitamin B12 deficiency in patients who underwent
      a Roux-en-Y gastric bypass.

      Daily oral use of vitamin B12 tablets are may be as effective as vitamin B12 injections.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
